          {
            "title": "Class Methods",
            "id": 88765,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Classes can have functions too, which are known as <strong>methods</strong> when they're inside of a class. Like the <code>bark()</code> method here.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.bark()\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"Bark\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Self",
            "id": 89349,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p><code>self</code> is a special keyword that we need to use inside our class definition. We pass <code>self</code> as the first parameter to all the methods we add.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.bark()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"49\" endIndex=\"53\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"if\" /></content></option><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"while\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Bark\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>self</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Self",
            "id": 88784,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We use <code>self</code> as a parameter in the class methods so that we can access the class variables like <code>color</code> and <code>legs</code> inside the methods.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  legs = \" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"display_color\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.color)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"display_legs\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.legs)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.display_color()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.display_legs()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"123\" endIndex=\"127\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"brown\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"4\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>self</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Self",
            "id": 89350,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Inside <code>display_color()</code>, <code>self.color</code> is how we access the value of the class variable <code>color = \"brown\"</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  legs = \" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"display_color\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.color)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"display_legs\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.legs)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.display_color()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.display_legs()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"123\" endIndex=\"127\" /><option startIndex=\"127\" endIndex=\"128\" /><option startIndex=\"128\" endIndex=\"133\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"brown\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"4\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>self</code>, followed by <code>.</code>, and finally <code>color</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Self",
            "id": 89351,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Without using <code>self</code> we wouldn't be able to access the class variables as they are declared outside of the class method's scope.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  legs = \" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"display_color\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.color)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"display_legs\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.legs)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.display_color()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.display_legs()\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"brown\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"4\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Class Methods",
            "id": 88785,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To use a class method, it's the same as using a class variable, except we need to add parentheses. Like here with <code>rocky.bark()</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(rocky.color)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.bark()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"117\" endIndex=\"122\" /><option startIndex=\"122\" endIndex=\"123\" /><option startIndex=\"123\" endIndex=\"127\" /><option startIndex=\"127\" endIndex=\"128\" /><option startIndex=\"128\" endIndex=\"129\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"brown\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Bark\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>rocky</code> followed by <code>.</code> and then <code>bark</code>, <code>(</code>, <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question 1",
            "id": 88787,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Which is true about a class definiton?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">You can create functions and variables in a class definition</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">You can only create variables in a class definition</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">You can create functions and variables in a class definition.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question 2",
            "id": 88819,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>How do we access <code>rocky</code>'s method <code>print_color</code>?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Dog\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"__init__\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    self.color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print_color\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(self.color)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Dog()\" /></content></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"><code>rocky.print_color()</code></item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\"><code>print_color(rocky)</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>rocky.print_color()</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
