            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Why do we need to use the keyword <code>self</code> when accessing class variables from inside a method?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">We need to use <code>self</code> to make class variables scope accessible inside a method  </item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">As we need to use <code>self</code> to create any variables in a class</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">We need to use <code>self</code> to make class variables scope accessible inside a method  .</p></body></html>"
